    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_10_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_10",
      "description": "Offered is a driver-focused 2004 BMW M3 (E46) featuring the iconic S54 3.2L naturally aspirated inline-six. This unit delivers linear power delivery with its high-pressure double-VANOS variable valve timing and six individual throttle bodies. The chassis remains taut, benefitting from a Getrag 6-speed manual transmission and a factory-spec M-Variable differential lock for optimal mechanical grip. Recent preventative maintenance includes a cooling system overhaul and inspection of the rear subframe mounting points. While showing honest patina consistent with its mileage, the suspension geometry remains true, and the hydraulic steering rack provides the communicative feedback enthusiasts crave. A mechanically robust example ready for the twisties.",
      "price": 34500.0,
      "reputation": 0.5,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 29
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_9_listing_3",
      "firm_id": "sybil_9",
      "description": "Used car. Good condition. Well-maintained. Clean interior. Mechanically sound. Priced to move.",
      "price": 28500.0,
